&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Decima International is a professional services company, providing project management and controls services to clients in the United States and the Middle East. Our mission is to become the premier professional services provider across all industry sectors we are engaged in. To accomplish this, Decima International’s founders established a simple yet powerful formula:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Approach each client engagement as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;partnership&lt;/strong&gt;, create an environment that attracts the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;most talented professionals&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and allows them to flourish, and regulate&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;growth&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to maintain&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in our service standards.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in a long and rewarding career working with high-profile clients on some of the most challenging projects in the world, then Decima is where you belong. At Decima, you will be able to explore incredible growth and professional development opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a driven and capable &lt;strong&gt;Controls Engineer / Controls Operations Subject Matter Expert&lt;/strong&gt; to support mission-critical data center projects in KSA. This role will provide technical expertise across controls design review, commissioning, operational readiness, facility operations, and controls integration for complex data center environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate has strong direct data center experience and a deep understanding of building automation systems, building management systems, electrical power monitoring systems, SCADA, PLC-based control systems, HMI, and industrial control systems supporting Tier III and Tier IV facilities. The candidate should be capable of reviewing control systems for operability, maintainability, reliability, cybersecurity, resiliency, and alignment with client operational standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on, client-facing technical role focused on control system performance, operational risk, automation strategy, procedure development, commissioning support, and operational readiness. The role requires strong technical writing, communication, and stakeholder management skills, including the ability to develop, review, and validate Standard Operating Procedures, Emergency Operating Procedures, Methods of Procedure, and Sequences of Operation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
